      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LEKTRA HARMONY (1) has a terrific record this track and trip with three wins and one placing from four starts. Was out of the placings last time (26.70) at Warrnambool in a Grade 5, finishing eighth and beaten 17 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. PAW CHRISTIE (3) made light work of a wide draw last time with a slick early sectional but gathered in and had to settle for the minors, finishing second (25.96) at Geelong over 460m. The form from her last run is stacking up nicely. Expected to feature again. NOSEY PARKER (7) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (23.70) at this track behind On The River in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Boasts a strong record from this draw with four wins and three minor placings from 10 starts. Can measure up. CABAO LAPIS (2) missed the placings here last start but is well-placed to bounce back.",
